Here’s a compact **print‑stylesheet block** that locks page geometry, header, and footer positions so exported or printed versions keep the “calm” spacing you’ve defined.

```css
/* Calm Dialogue Workbook – Print Layout */

/* Page box and margins */
@page {
  size: A4;                           /* or "Letter" for U.S. versions */
  margin: 1in 0.75in 1in 0.75in;      /* top, right, bottom, left */
}

/* General body text */
@media print {
  body {
    font-family: "Source Sans Pro", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
    font-size: 10pt;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: #000000;
    background: #FFFFFF;
  }

  /* Remove interactive or screen‑only items */
  nav, .sidebar‑controls, .buttons {
    display: none !important;
  }

  /* Header block */
  header {
    position: running(header);
    font-size: 9pt;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #5BA4CF;
    border-bottom: 0.5pt solid #A0A0A0;
    margin-bottom: 0.25in;
    padding-bottom: 0.15in;
  }

  /* Footer block */
  footer {
    position: running(footer);
    font-size: 8pt;
    color: #555555;
    border-top: 0.5pt solid #A0A0A0;
    margin-top: 0.25in;
    padding-top: 0.1in;
    text-align: right;
  }

  /* Page numbers (for PDF generators that support counters) */
  @bottom-right {
    content: counter(page);
    font-size: 8pt;
    color: #777777;
  }

  /* Sidebar call‑outs */
  .sidebar {
    float: right;
    width: 40%;
    background: #F4F5F6;
    border: 0.5pt solid #A0A0A0;
    padding: 0.25in;
    margin: 0 0 0.25in 0.25in;
  }

  /* Tables */
  table {
    border-collapse: collapse;
    width: 100%;
    margin: 0.2in 0;
  }
  th, td {
    border: 0.5pt solid #A0A0A0;
    padding: 0.07in 0.1in;
  }
  th {
    background: #E6EEF3;
    color: #3B8686;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
}
```

**Usage**
1. Attach it as `print.css` and reference it in your HTML/PDF export profile.  
2. Many layout engines (PrinceXML, Vivliostyle, WeasyPrint) support `running(header/footer)` and page counters; others will simply treat them as static blocks.  
3. Adjust `margin` values if your printer requires extra binding space.

This stylesheet locks the workbook’s visual breathing room—ample white space, restrained color, and balanced typography—so printed copies look calm and consistent with the digital version.
